he hall, began to descend the low stone steps for the last time. The huge casement on the landing was wide open onto the back courtyard, and down in the yard an itinerant baritone was roaring a Russian Volga song in German.

Listening to that voice, vibrant as springtime itself, and glancing at the colored design on the open windowpane—a bunch of cubic roses and a peacock’s fan—Ganin felt he was free.

